        <h1 class="essay-title">
          <em>Insignificantly Significant</em> <span class="essay-year">(2020)</span>
        </h1>
        
        <div class="essay-body">
          <p>
            In 2020, a handwritten memory of mine was memorialised on a bronze plaque in Enmore Park, Sydney, as part of Sam Holt's <a href="https://www.instituteforpublicart.org/case-studies/insignificantly-significant/" target="_blank" class="about-link"><em>Insignificantly Significant</em></a> public art project. The plaque is fixed to the concrete slab beside the bench where I used to sit.
          </p>
          <p>
            The memory is from 2016: "I'd bought half a dozen oysters I couldn't afford and I ate them alone in the park. Sunday. Watching groups of friends meet and children play I felt both together and alone. I had just moved out of home."
          </p>
        </div>

